  "description": "A rinse cycle is a routine of rinsing seeds or [sprouts](./sprout.md) with clean water to reduce microbial growth and maintain freshness during the growing process. In [home gardening](../index.md), rinse cycles are the primary food-safety intervention available to growers who lack commercial-scale sanitation equipment.",
